Key Match Events: David Wiese smashed 13 runs off four balls in the first super over
Wiese restricted Oman to just ten runs in the super over
Namibia needed 18 runs from 18 balls with seven wickets in hand, then just seven runs from the last nine balls to win
Post-Match Reflections: Namibia are playing in the T20 World Cup for only the third time after previous appearances in 2021 and 2022
Miscellaneous Highlights: Mehran Khan gave his side a shot at super over victory with figures of 3/7 in his three overs
Ruben Trumpelmann bagged four wickets, including two with his first two balls
Namibia skittled Oman for 109 all out in 19.4 overs
